    {
      "id": "comment-Homebrew/homebrew-core-47935-115",
      "type": "issue_comment",
      "ts": "2019-12-17T10:41:33Z",
      "repo": "Homebrew/homebrew-core",
      "semantic": null,
      "data": {
        "issueNumber": 47935,
        "issueTitle": "i386-elf-binutils, i386-elf-gcc: add 64-bit support",
        "body": "@fxcoudert \r\nSo there's a new question, if we use target `x86_64-elf`, and we are going to get something like `x86_64-elf-ld`, `x86_64-elf-as`, instead of `i386-elf-xxx`\r\nIs that allowed?"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "comment-Homebrew/homebrew-core-47935-116",
      "type": "issue_comment",
      "ts": "2019-12-16T14:40:19Z",
      "repo": "Homebrew/homebrew-core",
      "semantic": null,
      "data": {
        "issueNumber": 47935,
        "issueTitle": "i386-elf-binutils, i386-elf-gcc: add 64-bit support",
        "body": "@fxcoudert \r\n\r\nHi, I have an question, when I test i386-elf-gcc with the following configure:\r\n```\r\nsystem \"../configure\", \"--target=i386-elf\",\r\n                             \"--enable-targets=all\",\r\n                             \"--prefix=#{prefix}\",\r\n                             \"--without-isl\",\r\n                             \"--enable-multilib\",\r\n                             \"--disable-werror\",\r\n                             \"--without-headers\",\r\n                             \"--with-as=#{Formula[\"i386-elf-binutils\"].bin}/i386-elf-as\",\r\n                             \"--with-ld=#{Formula[\"i386-elf-binutils\"].bin}/i386-elf-ld\",\r\n                             \"--enable-languages=c,c++\"\r\n```\r\nthe error is:\r\n```\r\n> i386-elf-gcc tmp.c -c -m64\r\n> cc1: 对不起，尚未实现：未编译入对 64 位模式的支持\r\n```\r\nWhich means that 64-bit is not supported.\r\nI am not sure if I made a mistake, but in fact, I succeeded with target=x86_64.\r\nDo you have any suggestions?"
      }
    },
